description.plain:
Correct credits:
Written by John Holt for The Paragons
Produced by Noel Saucedo of The Haus-a-Holics and John Pro

The original song was released in 1971 by The Paragons (Holt was the lead singer), which was a ska band from Jamaica. Gregory Isaacs, a Jamaican reggae singer, covered the song in 1978. Blondie covered the song in 1980 for their 5th album, Autoamerican. English girl group Atomic Kitten also covered the song in 2002.
